{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The conversation history passed to the LLM is trimmed to the most recent 10 messages when the full history exceeds the context window.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: A pure unit test of a trim helper can miss wiring bugs (wrong order, wrong field, not applied before LLM call). REAL-INFRA: no OS/network required. MOCK-HIDE: mocking only the helper can hide payload-construction failures. LLM-DEP: not dependent on model quality.","test_description":"Run the real request handler + prompt-building modules with 15 prior messages and a fake LLM transport that records the outbound payload. Assert only the latest 10 messages are sent, in correct order, with expected roles/content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The generated response addresses the customer's question rather than producing a generic or off-topic reply.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: correctness is about semantic relevance/quality of model output, which a mock cannot represent. MOCK-HIDE: a mocked model can always return a perfect answer and miss real off-topic failures. MULTI-STEP: single generation quality check, not a full multi-agent pipeline.","test_description":"Send representative customer questions to the production-like LLM endpoint and evaluate relevance against a rubric (or human-labeled set). Fail when responses are generic/off-topic above threshold across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.85,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The tone re-check correctly identifies when a response is too formal for a casual-tier customer and triggers regeneration.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: 'too formal' detection quality depends on real model judgment. MOCK-MISS/MOCK-HIDE: mocked classifier or rule-based stand-in can miss real misclassification. MULTI-STEP: regeneration trigger is coupled, but the core failure boundary is model tone judgment.","test_description":"Use casual-tier prompts that induce formal first drafts, run real tone-check logic with real model classification (or real LLM-based evaluator), and assert regeneration is triggered at required rate on labeled examples.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.15}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full exchange (user message, generated response, any regenerations) is persisted to the database with correct timestamps.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: in-memory mocks can miss ORM/schema/transaction/timestamp mapping issues. REAL-INFRA: needs local DB/filesystem I/O but not external OS/network behavior beyond process-local infra. LLM-DEP: not model-quality dependent.","test_description":"Execute a chat request through service modules against a real test DB. Trigger a regeneration path and verify stored rows include user message, first draft, regenerated draft, linkage fields, and monotonic correct timestamps.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the tone check triggers regeneration, the second response replaces the first — the customer never sees the rejected draft.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: unit tests can miss orchestration bugs where draft leaks through API/stream path. REAL-INFRA: can be validated in-process via endpoint/service integration. LLM-DEP: trigger condition can be forced deterministically; core requirement is replacement/visibility control.","test_description":"Run end-to-end service flow with deterministic doubles forcing tone-check failure then regeneration. Assert API/streamed customer-visible output contains only second response and that first draft is marked internal/rejected.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
